### 6.2 Animated Grid Card

**Card:** `AnimatedGrid extends CardDef`

**Purpose:** Reusable animated card grid background that can be composited into sections.

**Fields:**
- `gridColumns: NumberField` â€” Number of columns (default: 6)
- `gridRows: NumberField` â€” Number of rows (default: 4)
- `animationSpeed: StringField` â€” "slow" | "medium" | "fast"
- `cardOpacity: NumberField` â€” 0.0 to 1.0 (default: 0.3)
- `accentColor: StringField` â€” Hex color for highlight cards

**Template Features:**
- CSS Grid layout with specified columns/rows
- Randomly highlighted cards with accent color
- Subtle animation using CSS animations
- Fully self-contained with scoped styles

**Usage:**
This card is designed to be composited into other sections as a background layer:

```gts
// In hero-section.gts
export class HeroSection extends SectionCard {
  @field backgroundGrid = linksTo(() => AnimatedGrid);

  static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
    <template>
      <section class="hero-section">
        {{#if @model.backgroundGrid}}
          <div class="background-layer">
            <@fields.backgroundGrid @format="isolated" />
          </div>
        {{/if}
        <div class="hero-content">
          <!-- Hero content here -->
        </div>
      </section>
    </template>
  };
}
```

**AnimatedGrid Template:**

```gts
export class AnimatedGrid extends CardDef {
  static displayName = 'Animated Grid';

  @field gridColumns = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 6; }
  });

  @field gridRows = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 4; }
  });

  @field animationSpeed = contains(StringField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 'medium'; }
  });

  @field cardOpacity = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 0.3; }
  });

  @field accentColor = contains(StringField, {
    computeVia: function() { return '#00ffba'; }
  });

  static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
    get totalCells() {
      return (this.args.model?.gridColumns ?? 6) * (this.args.model?.gridRows ?? 4);
    }

    get cellArray() {
      return Array.from({ length: this.totalCells }, (_, i) => i);
    }

    <template>
      <div class="animated-grid" style="
        --grid-columns: {{@model.gridColumns}};
        --grid-rows: {{@model.gridRows}};
        --card-opacity: {{@model.cardOpacity}};
        --accent-color: {{@model.accentColor}};
      ">
        {{#each this.cellArray as |index|}}
          <div class="grid-cell" data-index={{index}}></div>
        {{/each}}
      </div>

      <style scoped>
        .animated-grid {
          width: 100%;
          height: 100%;
          display: grid;
          grid-template-columns: repeat(var(--grid-columns, 6), 1fr);
          grid-template-rows: repeat(var(--grid-rows, 4), 1fr);
          gap: 1rem;
          padding: 2rem;
        }

        .grid-cell {
          background: rgba(255, 255, 255, var(--card-opacity, 0.3));
          border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
          border-radius: var(--radius, 0.5rem);
          transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        /* Highlight random cells with accent color */
        .grid-cell:nth-child(3),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(7),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(12),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(19) {
          background: var(--accent-color);
          box-shadow: 0 0 2rem var(--accent-color);
        }

        /* Subtle animation */
        @keyframes pulse {
          0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
          50% { opacity: 0.6; }
        }

        .grid-cell {
          animation: pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite;
          animation-delay: calc(var(--grid-columns) * 0.1s * random());
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

**Instance Example:**

```json
// examples/AnimatedGrid/hero-background.json
{
  "data": {
    "type": "card",
    "id": "https://realms.../examples/AnimatedGrid/hero-background",
    "meta": {
      "adoptsFrom": {
        "module": "../animated-grid",
        "name": "AnimatedGrid"
      }
    },
    "attributes": {
      "gridColumns": 6,
      "gridRows": 4,
      "animationSpeed": "slow",
      "cardOpacity": 0.25,
      "accentColor": "#00ffba"
    }
  }
}
```

**Why This Pattern?**

1. **Reusability** â€” AnimatedGrid can be used in multiple sections
2. **Independent Editing** â€” Grid parameters can be edited separately
3. **Composition Over Inheritance** â€” Sections compose cards rather than hardcoding features
4. **Clean Separation** â€” Background logic is isolated from hero content logic
5. **Testable** â€” AnimatedGrid can be previewed/tested independently

