## Orchestrator-to-Section CSS API

The `SiteLayoutCard` orchestrator communicates layout parameters to section cards via CSS custom properties. This creates an explicit contract between the site layout and individual sections.

### How It Works

The orchestrator sets CSS variables on the sections container, which sections read via `var()` in their scoped styles:

```gts
// In boxel-home-layout.gts - SiteLayoutCard template
static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
  <template>
    <div class="site-layout">
      <nav class="toolbar">...</nav>

      <!-- Sections container defines the API -->
      <main class="sections-container">
        {{#each @fields.sections as |sectionField|}}
          <sectionField.content @format="isolated" />
        {{/each}}
      </main>
    </div>

    <style scoped>
      .sections-container {
        /* Define section API variables */
        --section-padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
        --section-padding-inline: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);
        --section-max-width: 1400px;
        --section-gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem);

        /* Optional: Different padding for specific section types */
        --hero-padding-block: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 8rem);
        --footer-padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      }
    </style>
  </template>
};
```

### Sections Consume the API

Each section card reads these variables in its own scoped styles:

```gts
// In hero-section.gts - HeroSection template
static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
  <template>
    <section class="hero-section">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <!-- Section content -->
      </div>
    </section>

    <style scoped>
      .hero-section {
        /* Read orchestrator-provided padding */
        padding-block: var(--hero-padding-block, var(--section-padding-block, 4rem));
        padding-inline: var(--section-padding-inline, 1.5rem);

        /* Center content with max-width */
        max-width: var(--section-max-width, 1400px);
        margin-inline: auto;
      }

      .hero-content {
        /* Internal layout can still use its own spacing */
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 2rem;
      }
    </style>
  </template>
};
```

### The CSS Variable Contract

**Required Variables** (orchestrator must define):
- `--section-padding-block` â€” Vertical padding (top/bottom)
- `--section-padding-inline` â€” Horizontal padding (left/right)
- `--section-max-width` â€” Content max-width for centering
- `--section-gap` â€” Spacing between sections

**Optional Variables** (section-specific overrides):
- `--hero-padding-block` â€” Extra vertical space for hero
- `--footer-padding-block` â€” Tighter footer padding
- `--catalog-columns` â€” Grid columns for catalog
- `--section-bg` â€” Background color override

### Example: Different Padding Per Section Type

```css
/* In SiteLayoutCard orchestrator */
.sections-container {
  --section-padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
  --section-padding-inline: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);

  /* Section-specific overrides */
  --hero-padding-block: clamp(5rem, 12vw, 10rem);     /* More breathing room */
  --video-padding-block: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem);      /* Tighter for media */
  --footer-padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);     /* Compact footer */
  --catalog-padding-inline: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem);   /* Extra horizontal space */
}
```

```gts
// HeroSection uses the override
padding-block: var(--hero-padding-block, var(--section-padding-block));

// VideoDemoSection uses its override
padding-block: var(--video-padding-block, var(--section-padding-block));

// Generic section uses base value
padding-block: var(--section-padding-block);
```

### Benefits of This Pattern

1. **Centralized Control** â€” Orchestrator controls all section spacing from one place
2. **Consistent Rhythm** â€” All sections follow the same vertical rhythm by default
3. **Easy Override** â€” Individual sections can opt into different spacing when needed
4. **Responsive by Default** â€” `clamp()` values scale automatically
5. **Theme Integration** â€” Can reference theme variables:
   ```css
   --section-padding-block: var(--boxel-sp-xxxl, 4rem);
   ```

### Full Example: Three Sections with Coordinated Padding

```gts
// boxel-home-layout.gts
export class SiteLayoutCard extends CardDef {
  static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
    <template>
      <div class="site-layout">
        <main class="sections-container">
          {{#each @fields.sections as |sectionField|}}
            <sectionField.content @format="isolated" />
          {{/each}}
        </main>
      </div>

      <style scoped>
        .sections-container {
          /* Base API */
          --section-padding-block: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem);
          --section-padding-inline: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);
          --section-max-width: 1400px;

          /* Per-section overrides */
          --hero-padding-block: clamp(5rem, 12vw, 10rem);
          --catalog-padding-inline: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem);
          --footer-padding-block: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);

          /* Layout */
          display: flex;
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: 0; /* Sections handle their own spacing */
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

